[
    {
        "content": "<p>I suggest that we rename lemmas about <code>_ ×ˢ _</code> to <code>*_sprod_*</code> (creating lots of deprecated aliases). Currently, lemmas for sets, subgroups etc use <code>prod</code> while lemmas for <code>Finset</code> use <code>product</code> to avoid conflict with <code>Finset.prod</code>.</p>",
        "id": 473153033,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727454098
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe <code>cartProd</code> instead?</p>",
        "id": 473153311,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1727454139
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What does it stand for?</p>",
        "id": 473153488,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727454180
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>\"<strong>cart</strong>esian <strong>prod</strong>uct\"</p>",
        "id": 473153926,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1727454260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Then we should rename <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SProd#doc\">docs#SProd</a> too.</p>",
        "id": 473154007,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727454277
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But <code>Prod</code> is a cartesian product too, so it doesn't help to disambiguate.</p>",
        "id": 473154376,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727454355
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there any need to disambiguate from <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Prod#doc\">docs#Prod</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 473154924,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1727454466
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We could rename <code>Finset.prod</code> to <code>Finset.iMul</code>, with the reasoning <code>sup : iSup :: mul : iMul</code></p>",
        "id": 473246078,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1727476425
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>More seriously, it's tempting to let the things about <code>Prod</code> claim the <code>prod</code> name, and rename the nary multiplication, with <code>product</code> being the least controversial option I can think of</p>",
        "id": 473246217,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1727476536
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And what about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SProd#doc\">docs#SProd</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 473246326,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727476579
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We have things like <a href=\"http://LinearMap.prod\">LinearMap.prod</a> (as in <code>Prod</code>) to consider too</p>",
        "id": 473246347,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1727476595
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>IMHO, we should rename lemmas/defs like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LinearMap.prod#doc\">docs#LinearMap.prod</a> to <code>prodMk</code></p>",
        "id": 473246420,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727476669
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>With <code>prodMap</code> <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Prod.map#doc\">docs#Prod.map</a> being another contestant for the name <code>prod</code> here.</p>",
        "id": 473246491,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727476699
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Whoops, prodMap is the one I meant to suggest</p>",
        "id": 473246552,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1727476751
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, it's not clear from the which one <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LinearMap.prod#doc\">docs#LinearMap.prod</a> is, which is a good reason to rename it.</p>",
        "id": 473246651,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727476820
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you take the \"sets are functions\" view, then SProd and prodMap are really the same operation</p>",
        "id": 473246668,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1727476837
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, it would be nice to have a common API for these constructions but my attempt at creating a common data structure for <code>*FunLike</code> failed.</p>",
        "id": 473246698,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727476873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>E.g., it would be nice to have a generic lemma in place of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submonoid.gc_map_comap#doc\">docs#Submonoid.gc_map_comap</a> etc</p>",
        "id": 473250772,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1727479629
    }
]